    <body>
        <div class="tip">
            <p class="tipInDiv" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #a5910a;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Tip: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">If you are creating custom templates and you edit the first-level heading (labeled "Chapter 1" in most templates), be sure that the ChapterHeading bookmark does not get deleted. The ChapterHeading bookmark is necessary for Doc-To-Help to know where to insert content when building output. If it is deleted, you may end up with duplicate content. </p>
            <p>To do this in Word, select the <span class="Emphasis">Insert</span> ribbon, then click <span class="Emphasis">Bookmark</span>. The Bookmarks dialog opens. If the ChapterHeading bookmark is not listed in the dialog, you can add it. If it is already listed, you do not need to do anything. For more information, see the Microsoft Word online Help.</p>
        </div>
